author: julianfoad
msg: Like other commands where a peg revision is not meaningful, make 'svn
export' error out if there is any non-empty peg specifier on the target
path (that is, the second path, the local destination), rather than just
ignoring any peg specifier given there.
This fixes one more case that was missed in r1196005 and r1196050. Related
"Cannot add or commit 'dir/@file.txt'" and to issue #3651
not eat peg revision within copy target path".
(svn_cl__export): Reject any non-empty peg revision specifier on the target.
